          "ADD-RES": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                ". Metallic Ge ( 17 g weight, 3 mm thickness, 27 mm",
                "distance from neutron source target) was irradiated.",
                "Gamma radiation with energy 0.157+-0.01 MeV and",
                "HL=(16+-1) msec was detected. The cross section for",
                "production of 0.17-MeV metastable level was determined",
                "to be 0.3 b. Authors assume that it belongs to one of",
                "isomers of Ge or Ga.",
                ". Y(2)O(3) oxide pressed as disc with 44 mm diameter,",
                "20 g weight, ~20 mm distance from neutron source target",
                "was irradiated. Activity with gamma energy",
                "0.24+-0.01 MeV and HL=(14+-1) msec was found.",
                "This is either isomer Y-89-M obtained in Y-89(n,n')",
                "reaction or Y-88-M isomer obtained in Y-89(N,2N)",
                "reaction."
              ]
            }
          ],
